" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-pdf\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-pdf\"></use></svg>Download PDF</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportTopicButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"singlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportSubtopicsButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"pdfWithChildren\" role=\"button\">Save selected topic and subtopics</a><a class=\"zDocsExportItem zDocsExportBundleButton\" href=\"#\" id=\"wholeBundlePdf\" role=\"button\">Save entire publication</a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicShare zDocsShareButton\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-expanded=\"false\" aria-label=\"Share\" class=\"d-none d-lg-flex zDocsShareDialogButton\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" data-tooltip-content=\"Share\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none zDocsShareDialogButton\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-share\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-share\"></use></svg>Share</span><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu\"><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareEmail\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Email Link</span></a><a class=\"dropdown-item zDocsShareButton zDocsShareLink\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\"><span>Copy Link</span></a></div></div><div class=\"zDocsFeedback zDocsFeedback zDocsTopicFeedback\" role=\"listitem\"><span aria-label=\"Feedback\" class=\"zDocsFeedbackButton d-none d-lg-flex\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" data-tooltip-content=\"Feedback\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsTopicActionsTooltip\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg></span><span class=\"d-lg-none d-flex zDocsFeedbackButton\" data-backdrop=\"static\" data-return-focus=\"#zDocsTopicActionsMobile\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_main_2528199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" role=\"button\" tabindex=\"0\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-feedback\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-feedback\"></use></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Dez 19, 2025</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104hgn1665702678084.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hgn1665702678084.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/hgn1665702678084.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"hgn1665702678084\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n                       \n Implementing an Email Security Driver \n   </h1>\n<div class=\"body taskbody\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">You can implement a custom email security driver using the Security Driver API.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section context\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__context_w5159ab1b5b1_w5160ab1b5_w5161ab1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40763e1_d40764e1_d40765e1\">The API include file <span class=\"ph filepath\">zsecdrv.h</span> is located in <span class=\"ph filepath\">\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">InstallDir</var>/uniface/3gl/include</span>.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40766e1_d40767e1_d40768e1\">Compiled libraries for the drivers are provided in the <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/bin</span> (Windows) or <span class=\"ph filepath\">/common/lib</span> (Unix) directory of your Uniface installation:</p>\n<ul class=\"ul\">\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20381e1_d20382e1_d20383e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">zsecdrv</span>—Generic Security Driver\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20384e1_d20385e1_d20386e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">uauthlogin</span>—AUTH LOGIN security driver\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20387e1_d20388e1_d20389e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">uauthntlm</span>—AUTH NTML security driver\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20390e1_d20391e1_d20392e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">uauthsspi</span>—SSPI security driver\n </li>\n<li class=\"li\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20393e1_d20394e1_d20395e1\">\n<span class=\"ph filepath\">uauthxoauth2</span>—XOAUTH2 security drivers for POP and SMTP\n </li>\n</ul>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40769e1_d40770e1_d40771e1\">The C source files for these security drivers are\n            available as a sample on <a class=\"xref\" href=\"https://community.rocketsoftware.com/uniface-samples-111\" rel=\"external noopener\" target=\"_blank\">Rocket Community</a>.</p>\n<div class=\"div context\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__topic_d40775e1_d40776e1_d40777e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40778e1_d40779e1_d40780e1\">You can write your own security driver in any language that supports creating a shared library or DLL.</p>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40781e1_d40782e1_d40783e1\">To implement your own SMTP driver:</p>\n</div>\n</section>\n<section><ol class=\"ol steps\"><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20396e1_d20397e1_d20398e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40784e1_d40785e1_d40786e1\">Ensure that you understand the way the SMTP\n               driver works, including security context, the use of buffers, and the flow of API\n               calls. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"cru1665702678159.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cru1665702678159.html\" title=\"A security context is the complete security environment required for a secure connection to a mail server. It consists of one or more security drivers that are responsible for connection and authentication to the email server.\">Security Context</a>, <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ijk1665702678251.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ijk1665702678251.html\" title=\"When establishing or removing a security context, drivers prepare messages and receive replies of varying lengths. The caller provides static buffers for input and output, which the driver can use.\">Buffer Management for SMTP Security Drivers</a> and <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"nlv1665702678531.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/nlv1665702678531.html\" title=\"Calls to an SMTP security driver are issued by operations on the Uniface UPOPMAIL component. These have an equivalent 3GL implementation which handles the actual call.\">Flow of Calls to the SMTP Security Driver API</a>. </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20399e1_d20400e1_d20401e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Include the definitions provided by the API in your source file. For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"aqt1665702677943.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/aqt1665702677943.html\" title=\"Uniface provides an API for creating custom client/server and SMTP and POP security drivers. The API include files for the C compiler and libraries are provided in the Uniface/3gl directory.\">APIs: Security Driver</a>.\n                        </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20402e1_d20403e1_d20404e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\">Compile the source into a standard shared library for your platform, where the entry point function is an exported function that may be called. Refer to one of the sample make files provided.\n </span>\n</li><li class=\"li step stepexpand\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__li_d20405e1_d20406e1_d20407e1\">\n<span class=\"ph cmd\" id=\"hgn1665702678084__p_d40787e1_d40788e1_d40789e1\">Enable the security driver by declaring the entry\n               point of the driver in the <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"daw1665702678607.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/daw1665702678607.html\" title=\"Use the [USER_3GL] section of the assignment file to lists third-party components and Uniface 3GL extensions to be made available to Uniface.\">[USER_3GL]</a> section of the\n               application assignment file. </span>\n<div class=\"itemgroup info\">\n<p class=\"p\">For example, for Microsoft Windows:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">[USER_3GL]\nc:/uniface/bin/mysmtpsecdrv(MySMTPSecDrv)</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</li></ol></section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ktb1665702890698.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Support for 3GL Languages</a><p>Strictly speaking, the interface between Uniface and 3GL is not tied to any specific language. You should be able to use the language of your choice, as long as the certain conditions are met.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2528199\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "Implementing an Email Security Driver Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Dez 19, 2025 Summarize Uniface 10.4 Implementing an Email Security Driver You can implement a custom email security driver using the Security Driver API. The API include file zsecdrv.h is located in InstallDir /uniface/3gl/include . Compiled libraries for the drivers are provided in the /common/bin (Windows) or /common/lib (Unix) directory of your Uniface installation: zsecdrv —Generic Security Driver uauthlogin —AUTH LOGIN security driver uauthntlm —AUTH NTML security driver uauthsspi —SSPI security driver uauthxoauth2 —XOAUTH2 security drivers for POP and SMTP The C source files for these security drivers are available as a sample on Rocket Community . You can write your own security driver in any language that supports creating a shared library or DLL. To implement your own SMTP driver: Ensure that you understand the way the SMTP driver works, including security context, the use of buffers, and the flow of API calls. For more information, see Security Context , Buffer Management for SMTP Security Drivers and Flow of Calls to the SMTP Security Driver API . Include the definitions provided by the API in your source file. For more information, see APIs: Security Driver . Compile the source into a standard shared library for your platform, where the entry point function is an exported function that may be called. Refer to one of the sample make files provided. Enable the security driver by declaring the entry point of the driver in the [USER_3GL] section of the application assignment file. For example, for Microsoft Windows: [USER_3GL] c:/uniface/bin/mysmtpsecdrv(MySMTPSecDrv) Copy Related Links Support for 3GL Languages Strictly speaking, the interface between Uniface and 3GL is not tied to any specific language. You should be able to use the language of your choice, as long as the certain conditions are met. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}